This narrows it down a lot.

Your Redis value clearly contains `appId`, `codeVerifier`, `redirectUri`, and `createdAt`, but after conversion your log shows they become `null`.

That means the problem is **not Redis storage** anymore. It is **Map → AuthTransaction conversion**.

## What this usually means

Your `AuthTransaction` class is not shaped in a way Jackson can populate all fields correctly.

The most common causes are:

* missing no-args constructor
* missing setters
* field names not matching exactly
* using a builder-only or custom constructor pattern
* fields marked `final`

## What the class should look like

Use a plain POJO like this:

```java
import lombok.Data;
import lombok.NoArgsConstructor;
import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;

@Data
@NoArgsConstructor
@AllArgsConstructor
public class AuthTransaction {
    private String state;
    private String nonce;
    private String codeVerifier;
    private String appId;
    private String redirectUri;
    private String postLoginRedirectUrl;
    private Instant createdAt;
}
```

And make sure the JSON names match these field names exactly:

* `codeVerifier`
* `appId`
* `redirectUri`
* `postLoginRedirectUrl`
* `createdAt`

## Very important

If you are using any of these on `AuthTransaction`, remove them for now:

* `@Builder`
* custom constructors only
* `final` fields
* weird field names like `appID`

## Your conversion code should be

```java
if (value instanceof Map<?, ?>) {
    AuthTransaction tx = objectMapper.convertValue(value, AuthTransaction.class);
    log.info("converted tx={}", tx);
    return tx;
}
```

## Also make your `ObjectMapper` able to handle `Instant`

```java
@Bean
public ObjectMapper objectMapper() {
    ObjectMapper mapper = new ObjectMapper();
    mapper.registerModule(new JavaTimeModule());
    mapper.disable(SerializationFeature.WRITE_DATES_AS_TIMESTAMPS);
    return mapper;
}
```

## Why only `state` and `nonce` seem to appear

That usually happens when the class shape and the JSON don’t line up cleanly. Jackson partially binds what it can, then leaves the rest null.

